An All Progressives Congress (APC) chieftain in Gombe, Jamil Gwamna, has resigned from the party. The Sardaunan Gombe is Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer of Kano Electricity Distribution Company (KEDCO). His resignation letter dated February 1, 2022 was addressed to the APC chairman in Jekadafari Ward. Gwamna explained that he took the decision to leave after a series of consultations. “I write, with all sense of humility and respect, to notify you of my decision to resign from the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC). “I took the decision after wide consultations with my family, political associates, and my supporters.” Gwamna thanked the APC for the support, privileges he enjoyed, and wished the platform well. The KEDCO chief was one of Gombe PDP governorship aspirants during the 2019 political season. Observers believe Gwamna is returning to the party to seek its 2023 ticket.